I think you said is right. There will be some logic implement in different component.However, does the parent component need to consider all the details of the child component?

I think when I create a component.I would like to encapsulate all the logic related to this component inside the component.Because the logic should belong to the component.Next time, when use this component in new component, I just need to think about the logic of the new component.

Besides,most applications now require asynchronous requests.Getting status from parent component is very common.So some time I will use ugly way to make it work.

